# Verify Before Proceeding

**Don't assume correctness. Verify after each commit.**

## Verification Checklist

- [ ] `npm run typecheck` (zero errors)
- [ ] `npm test` (100% pass)
- [ ] No unresolved imports or syntax errors
- [ ] Integration test if applicable (call an MCP tool, etc.)

## If Verification Fails

Fix the code, don't work around it. Debug the issue:
- **Type error?** Update types or fix code (consciously)
- **Test failure?** Fix the code or the test (if the test is wrong)
- **Build error?** Find the root cause (missing export, wrong import, etc.)

Only after verification passes, move to the next feature.

## When Tooling Blocks You

If `npm` is unavailable:
1. Try alternatives (`bun`, `npx`, online TypeScript playground)
2. If no alternatives exist, escalate to the user
3. Don't ignore the problem and keep coding

